In a teleconference, President Biden thanked Reid Hoffman for hosting the event and for his generous support. He praised the unity of the Democratic Party and discussed the importance of the American Rescue Plan, which has provided vaccinations and financial assistance to millions of Americans. Biden also highlighted the bipartisan agreement on infrastructure and emphasized the need to invest in both physical and human infrastructure. He expressed concern about the assault on the right to vote and vowed to fight against any attempts to undermine it. Biden concluded by stating that America can win the future with the support and unity of its citizens.